<item>
            <title>[LU-10550] Resync support when file is in RDONLY state</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10550</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When some components are failed to resync due to various reasons, those components will still have &lt;tt&gt;STALE&lt;/tt&gt; bit set but the file status may become &lt;tt&gt;RDONLY&lt;/tt&gt;. In the current implementation it &apos;mistakenly&apos; doesn&apos;t allow to resync a mirrored file in &lt;tt&gt;RDONLY&lt;/tt&gt; status, which means those components won&apos;t get resynced until the next write comes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should allow to resync file again as long as there are stale components existing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
